{{short description|Australian philosopher}} {{Infobox philosopher |region = [[Western philosophy]] |era = [[Contemporary philosophy|21st-century philosophy]] |color = |image = |name = '''Adrian Walsh''' |birth_date = 1963 |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |school_tradition = [[Analytic philosophy|Analytic]] | institutions = [[University of New England (Australia)]] |main_interests = [[political philosophy]], [[applied ethics]], [[philosophy of economics]] | thesis_title = | thesis_url = | thesis_year = | doctoral_advisor = | doctoral_students = |notable_ideas = | spouse = | education = [[University of Melbourne]] (PhD), [[Flinders University]] (BA) | alma_mater = |influences = |influenced = |awards = research fellowships at the [[University of St Andrews]] and the [[University of Helsinki]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Adrian Walsh (University of New England / University of Helsinki) |url=https://blogs.helsinki.fi/mpp-seminar/2015/04/21/29-4-adrian-walsh-university-of-new-england-university-of-helsinki/ |website=Moral and Political Philosophy Research Seminar |accessdate=29 October 2018 |date=21 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Community of Fellows |url=https://ceppa.wp.st-andrews.ac.uk/people/community-of-fellows/ |website=University of St Andrews |accessdate=29 October 2018}}</ref> |website = https://www.une.edu.au/staff-profiles/hass/awalsh }}
'''Adrian J. Walsh''' (born 1963) is an Australian philosopher and Professor of [[Philosophy]] at the [[University of New England (Australia)]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Adrian Walsh |url=https://expertconnect.global/expert/Adrian-Walsh/5b3f44fa49827d59b4865ba5 |website=Expert Discovery Porta |accessdate=29 October 2018 |language=en}}</ref> He is known for his expertise on [[political philosophy]], [[philosophy of economics]] and [[applied ethics]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Adrian Walsh |url=http://www.well.ox.ac.uk/cpm/adrian-walsh |website=University of Oxford Centre for Personalised Medicine |accessdate=29 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Hope |first1=Simon |title=Neo-Aristotelian Social Justice: An Unanswered Question |journal=Res Publica |date=May 2013 |volume=19 |issue=2 |pages=157–172 |url=https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007%2Fs11158-013-9213-y |accessdate=29 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Peden |first1=William |title=Boundaries, blunders, and scientific imperialism |journal=Metascience |date=19 April 2018 |volume=27 |issue=3 |pages=457–460 |doi=10.1007/s11016-018-0317-z |url=https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s11016-018-0317-z |accessdate=29 October 2018 |language=en |issn=0815-0796}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=CLAASSEN |first1=RUTGER |title=Ethics, Money and Sport. This Sporting Mammon - by Adrian Walsh & Richard Giulianotti |journal=[[Journal of Applied Philosophy]] |date=15 January 2008 |volume=25 |issue=1 |pages=75–77 |doi=10.1111/j.1468-5930.2008.00399_2.x |url=https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/j.1468-5930.2008.00399_2.x |accessdate=29 October 2018 |language=en |issn=0264-3758}}</ref> Walsh is an Associate Editor of the ''[[Journal of Applied Philosophy]]''.<ref>{{cite web |title=Journal of Applied Philosophy : |url=https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/page/journal/14685930/homepage/editorialboard.html |website=onlinelibrary.wiley.com |accessdate=29 October 2018 |language=en}}</ref>
