{{other people||Edward Reed (disambiguation)}} '''Edward Steven Reed''' (November 20, 1954 – February 14, 1997)<ref name="ssdi">''U.S., Social Security Applications and Claims Index, 1936-2007''</ref> was an American [[philosophy of science|philosopher of science]] and an [[ecological psychology|ecological psychologist]] in the vein of [[James J. Gibson]].<ref>Costall, A. (1999). "An [[Iconoclast]]'s Triptych. Edward Reed's Ecological Philosophy." ''Theory & Psychology'', 9, 411-416.</ref><ref>Mace, W.M. (1997). "In Memoriam: Edward S. Reed: November 20, 1954 – February 14, 1997." ''Ecological Psychology'', 9, 179-188.</ref>
Reed was born in [[New York, New York]]. He died in [[Mohnton, Pennsylvania]].<ref name="ssdi"/>
