'''El Mostafa Higazy''' is an [[Egyptian people|Egyptian]] philosopher who served as a political advisor to interim President [[Adly Mansour]]. He is also the founder of the Nasaq Foundation, an Egyptian [[think tank]] focused on issues of justice.
==Biography== Higazy studied engineering at [[University of Southern California|USC]],<ref> {{cite journal |first1=El Mostafa|last1=Higazy |first2=Amr S.|last2=Elnashai |first3=Mihran S.|last3=Agbabian |title=Behavior of Beam-Column Connections under Axial Column Tension |journal=Journal of Structural Engineering |date=May 1996 |page=501 |url=http://www.engr.psu.edu/amr_elnashai/docs/JournalArticles/39%20Higazy,%20Agbabian.pdf }}</ref> eventually earning a PhD in engineering and Strategic Management from USC.<ref name=NYU>{{cite web|url=https://its.law.nyu.edu/eventcalendar/index.cfm?fuseaction=main.detail&id=30940|title=Dr. Mostafa Higazy|publisher=NYU Law|accessdate=18 November 2015}}</ref> He founded NASAQ Foundation as a socio-political think tank,<ref name=Bio>{{cite web|url=http://www.nasaqfoundation.org/nasaq/the-founder|title=The Founder|publisher=NASAQ Foundation|accessdate=18 November 2015}}</ref> and subsequently founded ACME Corp as an economic arm of NASAQ.<ref name=Bio/>
Higazy received much notice for his role as Mansour's political advisor, proving himself a charismatic spokesman.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thinkmarketingmagazine.com/index.php/mostafa-hegazy-press-conference-effect-from-tv-to-social-media/|title=Mostafa Hegazy Press Conference Effect From TV to Social Media|work=Think Marketing|first=Hesham|last=Shata|accessdate=18 November 2015}}</ref>
